# Tenant data — never committed upstream.
# The private internal fork overrides this to commit snapshot/ and logs/ contents.
_data/snapshot/*
!_data/snapshot/.gitkeep
_data/logs/*
!_data/logs/.gitkeep

# Incident artifacts default-private. Journals, timelines, postmortems often
# contain context-specific data (timestamps, commit hashes, agent reasoning
# trails, tenant identifiers). The convention README explains the structure;
# individual incidents stay local unless engineers explicitly opt-in to
# publish via `!`-overrides per-incident.
#
# Production / internal-fork pattern: this gitignore only applies in the
# public skill kit. The internal fork is expected to override these rules
# (or use an internal-only gitignore via `.git/info/exclude`) so incident
# artifacts can be committed there for institutional memory.
_data/incidents/*
!_data/incidents/.gitkeep
!_data/incidents/README.md

# Zscaler help material is committed (not ignored) — it's the pinned bibliography
# our references/*.md cite. Attribution and provenance live in
# vendor/zscaler-help/NOTICE. See that file and vendor/zscaler-help/README.md.

# Playwright MCP session artifacts — browser snapshots, console logs, screenshots
# captured during JS-rendered page fetches. Useful mid-session, not worth committing.
.playwright-mcp/

# Claude Code session state.
.claude/settings.local.json

# Secrets
.env
*.env
!.env.example

# Python
__pycache__/
*.pyc
.venv/
.mypy_cache/
.ruff_cache/

# macOS
.DS_Store

# Rendered PDF packets (scripts/render-skill-pdf.sh output)
dist/
